value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic cytokinesis does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of mitotic cytokinesis is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of mitotic cytokinesis is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic cytokinesis begins later than normal.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which endocytosis does not occur. A phenotype may affect endocytosis of all cargoes, or of specific cargo such as a particular protein.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of endocytosis is decreased. A phenotype may affect endocytosis of all cargoes, or of specific cargo such as a particular protein.

label.value: decreased rate of endocytosis during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of endocytosis is decreased. A phenotype may affect endocytosis of all cargoes, or of specific cargo such as a particular protein.

label.value: delayed onset of endocytosis during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which endocytosis begins later than normal. A phenotype may affect endocytosis of all cargoes, or of specific cargo such as a particular protein.

A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of endocytosis is increased. A phenotype may affect endocytosis of all cargoes, or of specific cargo such as a particular protein.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which endocytosis is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cellular process phenotype in which the G1 to G0 transition is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype in which the G1 to G0 transition does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype in which the G0 to G1 transition begins later than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which fermentation is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which fermentation does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of fermentation is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of fermentation is increased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which fermentation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to antimycin A. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of antimycin A that allows wild type cells to grow.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of antimycin than normal.

label.value: decreased cell population growth on glycerol/ethanol carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which cell growth is decreased relative to normal in a medium containing glycerol and ethanol as the carbon sources.

definition.value: Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: abnormal protein localization during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype that affects the localization of a protein in a cell in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. A protein may be observed in a place where it is not normally found, absent from a place where it is normally found, or both.

definition.value: If this term is used, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

label.value: abnormal mitotic cell cycle arrest with replicated DNA

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested when cells have replicated genomic DNA, under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.

definition.value: Arrest with replicated DNA may occur between late S and G2/M; if only DNA content is measured, the arrest point cannot be determined with greater precision.

label.value: cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in G1 phase.

definition.value: For phenotypes affecting the G1 cell cycle that normally occurs in response to mating pheromone, see 'abnormal cell cycle arrest in response to pheromone' (FYPO:0000530) and its child terms.

label.value: cell cycle arrest at mitotic G2/M phase transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested at the mitotic G2/M phase transition.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which any process of protein complex assembly at the cellular level is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which MCM complex assembly is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the centromere of a chromosome is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the centromere and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the centromere of a chromosome is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to centromere during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the centromere of a chromosome is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to chromatin during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with chromatin and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: DNA content decreased during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of DNA in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased number of double-strand break sites during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites of double-strand breaks in DNA is greater than normal.

definition.value: Because Rad22 often accumulates at double-strand breaks, consider also annotating to 'increased number of Rad52 foci during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000972).

label.value: abnormal histone acetylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone acetylation is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal histone methylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which histone methylation is abnormal. All histone methylation may be affected, or methylation of specific sites on specific histones may be altered.

label.value: abnormal histone H3-K9 methylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal mitotic centromeric sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cohesion between centromeres of sister chromatids is abnormal during mitosis.

label.value: decreased mitotic centromeric sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cohesion between centromeres of sister chromatids is decreased during mitosis.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of intracellular transport is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mating type switching is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mating type switching does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of mating type switching is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of mating type switching is increased.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mating type switching is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of mitotic recombination is increased.
A cellular process phenotype in which one or both meiotic nuclear division(s) does not occur.
A cellular process phenotype in which one or both meiotic nuclear division(s) is arrested under conditions where arrest does not normally occur.
A cell population phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of one or both meiotic nuclear division(s) is decreased.
A cellular process phenotype in which one or both meiotic nuclear division(s) begins later than normal.
A cellular process phenotype in which the meiotic nuclear divisions are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
